INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '1ea19cc3-d982-4755-9412-a573ee0012ac',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$TensorFlow + scikit-learn — Plug Keras Models into sklearn Pipelines with SciKeras$escape$,
  $escape$TensorFlow users often rebuild preprocessing and cross-validation logic from scratch when sklearn already solves it. SciKeras (`scikeras.wrappers.KerasClassifier / KerasRegressor`) wraps any `tf.keras` model into a fully sklearn-compatible estimator, unlocking `Pipeline`, `GridSearchCV`, and `cross_val_score` without touching your model architecture.

Wrap your model factory in `KerasClassifier`, then slot it as the final step in a `Pipeline`. Upstream steps — `StandardScaler`, `ColumnTransformer`, custom transformers — run automatically before the Keras forward pass during both fit and predict. Hyperparameters prefixed with `model__` (e.g. `model__hidden_units`) flow through to your factory function, so `GridSearchCV` tunes architecture and learning rate alongside preprocessing choices in a single search.

Cross-validation via `cv=StratifiedKFold(5)` respects class balance and refits on every fold with proper weight initialization — no state leaks between folds. `gs.best_estimator_` returns the full pipeline, including fitted scaler, ready for `joblib.dump`. This pattern keeps TensorFlow's flexibility while leveraging sklearn's battle-tested model selection infrastructure.$escape$,
  $escape$from scikeras.wrappers import KerasClassifier
from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV, StratifiedKFold
import tensorflow as tf

def build_model(hidden_units=64, learning_rate=1e-3):
    model = tf.keras.Sequential([
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(hidden_units, activation="relu"),
        tf.keras.layers.Dense(1, activation="sigmoid"),
    ])
    model.compile(
        optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate),
        loss="binary_crossentropy", metrics=["accuracy"]
    )
    return model

pipe = Pipeline([
    ("scaler", StandardScaler()),
    ("model", KerasClassifier(model=build_model, epochs=30, verbose=0)),
])

param_grid = {
    "model__hidden_units": [32, 64],
    "model__learning_rate": [1e-3, 1e-4],
}
gs = GridSearchCV(pipe, param_grid, cv=StratifiedKFold(3), scoring="accuracy", n_jobs=-1)
gs.fit(X_train, y_train)
print(gs.best_params_, gs.best_score_)$escape$,
  $escape$python$escape$,
